Changelog
v.01
	- first useful build
	- added all Button Methods from K-API
	- added all Font Methods from K-API
v.02
    - Writeable completely reworked and is no hang anymore
    - text does 1 pixel space between each char
	- much more text and button related fixes
	- window now shows FPS and version in window title
	- you can now set the version of with window.setVersion(String)
    - window fixes
    - text and key input works better now
	- system time more accurate
v.03
    - running now don't needs a window as a parameter
	- added version and release info
    - re-added getVersionString form KAPI
	- added support for multithreading and improvements according to this
	- first beta test for playing sounds
	- button v1.6.2
v 0.4.0 r4
	- Input can now detect a tap and dragging
	- Scrolable is now working again(partially) (v1.2.2)
	- added Scrolable.touchUp for better dragging
v0.4.1 r5
    - you can now create a Texture& DrawMap with ByteBuffer as input
    - added Gaußianfiltermask method
    - added takeScreenshot methods in Grapphicfunktions
    - fixed a crash when pressing multimediakeys
    - updated Animation_scale_move_timed
v.0.4.2 r6 (28.08.2021)
    - added FileUtils.JSON
    - update for Writeable Button
    - the Method "Input.KeyDown" and "Input.keyTyped" has been updated for better keyboard behavior
    - added Spotify api things(ALPHASTATE)
v.0.4.3 r7 (07.09.2021)
    - the automatic button updates now can be disabled via Input.updateButtons(false);
    - some performance improvements for opengl
    - Button.getHang(i) now returns null if the hang not exists instead of indexoutofbounds exception
    - fixed Hang.isHovered()
v0.5.0 r8 (27.09.2021)
    - fixed Button related things
    - added Button.setDefFontColor and getDegFontColor
    - added many new GraphicFunktions like makeGrayScale
    - added Color constructor can now called with Color(float, float g, float b) before only int was possible
    - added Color.FloattoColor
    - added Color.getRandomColor
    - added Color.Vec3() returns RGB in a Vec3
    - added Color.Vec4() returns RGB in a Vec4
    - added Textures can now be rotated via shader eg Texture.setRotationX(60);
    - added Textures can now be flipped  via shader eg Texture.flipY(true);
	- added Textures can now be colorized via shader eg Texture.setColor(Color.Black) & Texture.setColorIntensity(1.5f)
	- added Button.setHeight
    - added Text.setHeight
v0.6.0 r9 (01.10.2021)
    - updated StatusBar
    - added collission Methods
    - added animation.TextureLoader
    - added Resolutions
    - added StatusBar
    - rearanged import paths com.karmorak.api not exists anymore its all .lib now
v.0.6.1 r10 (24.10.2021)
    - some Scrolbar adjustments (1.2.3)
    - fixed Text.toTexture
v.0.7.0 r11 (12.11.2021)
	Button.v1.7     - Hangs v.1.2
    - added text.getMinAbs return the smallest char-abs
    - added StatusBar.setAlpha (not working)
    - addded Button.setHangsInteractable and 2 similar methods
    - the hangs of a button now copy the color from their father
    - added Button.addHangs
    - reorganized Buttons Constructors
    - added Button.setThick
    - Button now has 3 predefined fonts (Offered_Font)
    - added TexutreConsturct.getX() and getY()
    - added KLIB.io
    - added DrawMap.buildCircle
    - added DrawMap.buildLine(its not perfect but works for the first)
    - writeable can now created as a hang  for itself (added new Methods for this in Button and Writeable)
    - DrawMap can now draw Circles;Lines and Triangles
    - added DrawMap.clear & DrawMap.clear(Color)
    - Texture and drawMaps can now be drawn without putting in a a batch with eg. Texture.render();
v0.7.1 r12
    - added getJSON3 and removed getJSON2
