v. 0.8.0.2 r20 (30.09.2023)
    - fixed an issue in JSON.get3
v. 0.8.0.3 r21 (30.11.2023)
    - Ownfont can now have comments behind a line
    - added ñ è ó as new char in font and new font georgia bold
    - Button can now change the default used font via .setDefault
    - OwnFonts now can set options in the file currently "opt_spacing15" & "opt_defscale0.09f"
v. 0.8.1 r22 (06.12.2023)
    - OwnFont v.1.4
    - FileUtils.writetoFile got more variety with the arguments you can hand over
v. 0.8.2 r23 (11.02.2024)
    - added DrawMap.drawFrom
    - added DrawMap.cut
    - added DrawMap.saveRenderImage
    - GraphicFunctions.saveDrawMap now can take a full path
    - added JNativeHook Library activated by KLIB.enableGlobalInput
    - added KLIB.system.SPI
    - added KLIB.io.setWallpaper
    - added FileUtils. move and copy
    - added FileUtils.convertImage
v. pre1 0.9.0 r24 (15.02.2024)
    - rewrote Texture Construct and DrawMap
    - many Functions of PNG moved to ImageLoader
    - all TextureConstructs now take String instead of URI or URL as Path
    - added Window.setDecorated
    - added Window.setHideWindow
    - fixed Window.setPosition (it wasn't updating before)
    - fixed GraphicFunctions.saveDrawMap
v. pre2 0.9.0 r25 (16.02.2024)
    - added WindowOptions to KLIB main
    - Window can no take more options before getting created (easier with the new WindowOptions)
    - update to lwjgl 3.3
    - update to Java 21.0.2(LTS)
    - reverted the change that all TextureConstructs now take Strings instead of URI or URL as Path
    - the arg -Dlibdebuglevel=1 can now set the debug level from a console
    - added KLIB.START replacing the need to create the window by urself and combining it with KLIB.INIT()
    - added KLIB.updateButtons is literally just a redirect to Input.updateButtons
    - WindowOptions got more options and is now Window storing them
v. pre3 0.9.0 r26 (13.11.2024)
--Window v3.0
    - Window and Running now support multiple windows
    - via KLIB.OPEN_WINDOW you can now open a new window or in Running/Window.open_newWindow
    - Running.window is not accessible anymore you can now get it with getWindow()
    - fixed window.setBounds
    - Window.setSize() does the same as set Bounds but named differently
    - added Window.getWidth getHeight getX und getY
    - you can now set the Viewport manually of a Window
    - you can now access the available monitors in Window with .monitors
    - you can change the monitor where the window is located on with Window.setMonitor
v. 0.9.0 r27 (23.01.2025)
    - SpotifyManager got new methods
    - added Spotify_Authv3
    - Authv3 saves the access token and uses the refresh token so its not neccessary to always login
    - improved writetoFile method when writing in mode2(replace on line)
    - fixed Button.isHovered not working
v. 0.9.1 r28 (01.02.2025)
    - added new FontTexture class
    - Button/Text/Font now uses FontTexture to draw
    - FileManager now uses the same formatting like the new Config class
    - all Texture Constructs are now able to set Min and Mag Filters
    - you can now set an default min and mag filter for TextureConstructs
    - added Spotify_Device class
v. 0.9.2 r29 (27.01.2026)
    - added isValue in prototype.Config
    - update to lwjgl 3.3.6
    - now using java 21.0.8
    - console now logs lwjgl version and got small rewrite
    - prototype.Config new funktion getKeys
    - added utils.PowerShell to execute a simple powershell-command and return as string
    - added MonitorNative to get monitor HardwareInfo
v.0.9.2.1
    - removed monitors[] list in Window cause its unused and should be replaced by a better solution
v. 1.0.0
    - update to Java 25.0.2 & lwjgl 3.4.0
    - Text and Button can now use special chars called with §§identifier
         - for this there was a huge rewrite needed of Font, OwnChar & Text
    - Button v1.9.0; Text v.1.5.0; ownFont v1.4.0
    - added Checkable
    - added Cycleable
    - added Textable (future replacement for writeable)
    - Button.isColliding is now Protected
    - some fixes to Expandable (v1.3.0)
    - DrawMap.fill got an new alterative method header
    - added DrawMap.drawOutline
    - Expandable now uses §§triple-dots as symbol to click on
    - renamed Scrolable to Scrollable (v2.0)
    - added Vector4i
    - every Vector class now implements the Vector interface
    - KLIB.INIT completely removed superseded by KLIB.START
    - deprecated getWidth_real got removed from Button
    - many small changes under the hood to hopefully improve stability and fix the jvm crashes
    - added ColorPreset and Colorable interface which is implemented by Color and ColorPreset
 v. 1.0.1
    - hopefully more improvements to reduce the HeapCorruption crashes that currently happening
    - einführung des GLTaskQueue

